title: Tucson mayor carjacked at gunpoint, city-owned Prius stolen
text:
Tucson mayor carjacked at gunpoint, city-owned Prius stolen The mayor was uninjured, but the carjacker is still at large, police said. Post to Facebook Tucson mayor carjacked at gunpoint, city-owned Prius stolen The mayor was uninjured, but the carjacker is still at large, police said.  //usat.ly/2mah0D3   Tucson mayor carjacked at gunpoint, city-owned Prius stolen USA Today Network Megan Janetsky, The Arizona Republic Published 8:18 p.m. ET Feb. 18, 2017 | Updated 1 minute ago Tucson Mayor Jonathan Rothschild (Photo: Tucson) 35 CONNECT COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
PHOENIX â€” Tucson Mayor Jonathan Rothschild was carjacked at gunpoint Saturday morning and his city-owned Toyota Prius was stolen, according to police. 
The mayor was uninjured, but the carjacker is still at large, Tucson police Sgt. Pete Dugan said. 
Rothschild was walking toward the Prius at about 11 a.m. when a man approached him, pointing a gun at him, Dugan said. 
The man demanded the keys to the car and fled after Rothschild handed them over. Witnesses reported that before carjacking the mayor, the man attempted to take another car in the area. Shortly before taking Rothschild's car, the man also approached a mail carrier in the area and pointed an object at him, Dugan said. The carrier was not sure the object pointed was a gun. 
Dugan said it doesn't appear Rothschild was specifically targeted.
